Sparta Systems, Inc. Key Developments

Sparta Systems Launches TrackWise® 9 Quality Management Software
Apr 11 17
Sparta Systems announced the launch of TrackWise 9, the latest version of its quality management software. This release introduced a new intuitive interface along with enhanced features to speed user adoption, and quality and compliance management throughout organizations. TrackWise 9 was built around insights from hundreds of users and feedback from seventy-five beta customers. The release offers a simple and seamless experience that makes it easy for casual users to track and act on quality events. It also introduced one-click data export, and a more robust automated validation package. Also, included in TrackWise 9 is an all new Intake capability. It allows employees to easily report potential quality or compliance issues from a simple, easy-to-use, cloud based interface. As a result, companies have greater visibility into potential quality incidents, and investigation and corrective actions can be initiated faster. TrackWise 9 continues the trend toward an integrated quality business network consisting of manufacturers, suppliers, distributors and other quality stakeholders. All of them are supported by capabilities in analytics, regulatory reporting, and quality processes that bring everything together in a single platform.


Sparta Systems Announces the Release of Stratas 3.0 Featuring TrackWise Intake
Apr 4 17
Sparta Systems announced the release of Stratas 3.0 featuring TrackWise Intake. The new capability is a web interface powered by Stratas 3.0 that enables a company to collect potential quality or compliance issues anywhere at any time from non-TrackWise users. TrackWise Intake leverages the Stratas platform to extend the reach of TrackWise through a web-based form that can be used to submit any type of quality events by those who don't normally access a company's quality management system (QMS). Companies have been searching for a means to effectively capture the information needed to investigate issues that would otherwise go unreported. The new capability empowers employees to contribute to company-wide quality initiatives while fostering a culture of collaboration and transparency. It also supports the shift towards an automated, all-digital approach to quality management processes. Stratas is a rapidly deployable QMS software platform that helps companies create, track, manage, and report on quality-related activities without the need to manage IT infrastructure. Stratas also enables companies to collaborate with suppliers on quality issues and provides full visibility throughout the supply chain. Additionally, suppliers and other partners can interact directly, leading to greater transparency, reduced risk, and improved control throughout the global supply chain. In addition to powering the TrackWise Intake feature, the Stratas 3.0 release expands administrator functionality, allowing greater control of user access and assignments throughout quality processes. It also adds new quality event workflows for partner-related activities, optimized for industry best practices.


Sparta Systems Releases Enhanced Document Management Solution for 123Compliance Cloud QMS Software
Feb 15 17
Sparta Systems announced the launch of enhanced document management functionality for its 123Compliance Quality Management Software. The release allows companies to improve collaboration on quality issues both internally and with external partners around the globe. 123Compliance Document Management enables companies to move away from outdated paper-based document management and reduce the number of separate document management systems required for compliance. This solution offers enhanced ease-of-use and simplified collaboration. 123Compliance Document Management improves quality collaboration and reduces risk of noncompliance. Updates to the solution accelerate review and approval processes by leveraging best practice workflows, organizing all documents into a single repository for ease of access across all sites and enabling the sharing of GxP documents among all key internal and external stakeholders. The robust document management feature allows authors, reviewers and approvers to access documents from any device and take the appropriate action. Moreover, a rule-based workflow is available to support established quality management processes. Documents can be templated for convenience and made to require electronic signatures.


