	SPARTA, Inc.

		
























Longstanding reputation for technical excellence and customer satisfaction
SPARTA, Inc., recently acquired by Parsons, provides world-class technical products and services to the defense, intelligence and homeland security sectors of the US federal government. SPARTA’s vision has been consistent since 1979—apply the best intellectual talent to help solve major national challenges. The company focuses on problems that require critical technical analysis, innovative computer science and engineering solutions, complex network analysis and architecture development, and expert acquisition support. SPARTA has a longstanding reputation for integrity, technical excellence, and customer satisfaction, which is founded in its commitment to the professional success of its employees.
SPARTA has more than 1,100 employees in offices across the US. Their core competencies include scientific, technical, and analytical skills applied to the development and application of models and simulations; the definition of complex system architectures; and the development of advanced algorithms, composite products, protocol processing, and information assurance technologies and methodologies. Parsons welcomes SPARTA and looks forward to an integration of its business units, which will enhance Parsons’ ability to provide world-class services in the areas of defense, intelligence, and national security.

Defense Business Unit
Integration of SPARTA’s Defense Business Unit will enable Parsons to offer an array of high-end scientific, systems engineering, and systems integration products and services for the Department of Defense (DoD) and the intelligence community. SPARTA has been instrumental in the design, development, fielding, and sustainment of effective weapons systems for more than 30 years and has proven domain expertise. Drawing on this background, Parsons will offer sophisticated and differentiated technical solutions to support the DoD and will maintain the prime position SPARTA has established on many long-term programs vital to our nation’s security. 
Key market segments include:

Advisory and Assistance Services (A&AS) 
System Engineering and Integration (SE&I) 
Information Assurance 
Training & Simulation 
Mission Support Services 

The Defense Business Unit has major offices in three primary locations: 

Arlington, Virginia 
Colorado Springs, Colorado 
Huntsville, Alabama 











National Security Business Unit
SPARTA’s National Security Business Unit will strengthen Parsons’ ability to provide unique solutions for intelligence production, information assurance, and computer network operations. Parsons will leverage SPARTA’s expertise in computer science and physics combined with their experience in analysis and mission operations to develop unique solutions to meet national intelligence requirements. SPARTA is an industry leader in network security, network operations, and cyber analytics. They bring to Parsons a comprehensive suite of cyber products and services that leverage reverse engineering, repeatable processes, advanced methods, and dedicated laboratories. The company’s full-spectrum cyber capabilities and solutions range from collection, processing, analysis, production, and dissemination of information to provisioning tools for network and information security. SPARTA has applied these tools to solve some of the most difficult and complex security issues using a novel approach that combines network defense techniques and active defensive capabilities to enable mission systems. SPARTA also provides high-end, specialized engineering services (hardware, software, systems, and security) in the scientific and technical intelligence domain. They employ nationally known experts in foreign material exploitation, associated production, and operational infrastructure including the implications on operational doctrine and tactics. SPARTA also employs experts in technical exploitation, reverse engineering activities, and modeling and simulation on various weapon systems. 









